\contentsline {table}{\numberline {28}{\ignorespaces The following user inputs are used to estimate customized herd-level lactation curve parameters. See the Methodology section of this document and the Lactation Curve Scientific Documentation for more detail about how these inputs are used with relation to daily milk production.}}{77}{table.28}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {29}{\ignorespaces The following inputs are used to determine the milk fat and milk protein percentages for each lactating cow}}{78}{table.29}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {30}{\ignorespaces The following inputs are used to constrain how much an average cow’s daily milk production will be reduced due to an inadequate ration. See the Methodology section of this document and the Ration Formulation scientific documentation for more detail about how these inputs are used with relation to daily milk production.}}{79}{table.30}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {31}{\ignorespaces Wood's Lactation Curve Base Parameters – These inputs provide the baseline values and variability for Wood’s lactation curve parameters as derived from \blx@tocontentsinit {1}\textcite {Li2022}.}}{85}{table.31}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {33}{\ignorespaces Adjustment Factors – These factors adjust the base parameters based on geographical, temporal, management, and parity considerations.}}{86}{table.33}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {35}{\ignorespaces Farm Specific 305-Day Milk Production — These inputs help tailor the lactation curve to the farm’s production targets and herd composition.}}{87}{table.35}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {36}{\ignorespaces Summary of important functions for the reproduction section. }}{88}{table.36}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {37}{\ignorespaces The following inputs are used to determine the probability and timing of cow death and sales events.}}{92}{table.37}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {38}{\ignorespaces Cumulative distribution function (CDF) values associated with the conditional probability that a sold animal is removed due to each group of issues and/or the conditional probability of death over time. Corresponds to the “probability” value for each cull reason in the animal input json file. The 'cull\_day\_count' array defines the segments of the CDF}}{97}{table.caption.10}%
